# Customizable Basket Naming

As CSA Admin welcomes organizations from more countries and languages, the word "basket" doesn't fit everyone. Some of you use "bags", "shares", or even "cones" and the app can now reflect that.

A new **Basket designation** setting is available in [Settings > General](/settings#general). It controls the terminology used for "basket" throughout the entire application, admin interface, member pages, invoices, delivery sheets, emails, and more.

## One Name Per Language

Multi-language organizations can also choose a **different naming for each language**. For example, a bilingual organization could use "Panier" in French and "Taschen" in German.

Here are all the available options:

| EN | FR | DE | IT | NL |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Basket | Panier | Korb | Cesta | Mand |
| Bag | Sac | Tasche | Borsa | Tas |
| Share | Part | Anteil | Parte | Deel |
| Package | Colis | Paket | Pacco | Pakket |
| Cone | Cornet | Tüte | Cono | Zak |
| Crate | Cagette | Kiste | Cassetta | Krat |

## ⚠️ Review Your Email Templates (If You Change It)

Changing the naming updates labels, menus, and documents automatically, but **[Automatic emails](/mail_templates) and [Newsletter templates](/newsletter_templates) content must be revised manually**. After changing the naming, review your templates to make sure they use the right terminology.

## A Note on Translations

Implementing this feature required extensive changes across the entire application to make all basket-related terminology dynamic. For most organizations, nothing changes, your current naming has been preserved. However, if you notice any translation that looks wrong or out of place, please [let me know](/support)!
